06/10/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EUPM chief Vincenzo Copolla, Republica Srpska Interior Minister Stanislav Cado and more than 20 police department spokespersons from different parts of BiH met in Sarajevo on Thursday (October 5th) to discuss law enforcement's responsibility to citizens. The forum aimed to co-ordinate efforts to draft a strategy establishing a national law enforcement agency, encourage dialogue between citizens and police, and boost public confidence in the police. 
Also Thursday, Sarajevo Mayor Semiha Borovac met with Belgrade counterpart Nenad Bogdanovic. Both were attending the 10th conference of the Union of Central and Southeast European Capitals, in Sarajevo. (RTRS, PBS, Fena - 05/10/06)
